  "doc_id": "17855",
  "text": "qRT-PCR of narP and cyaA showed no significant change in ΔycjW. A small subset of genes regulated by NarP was tested as downstream targets ( Supplementary   Fig. 4 ). Two genes, nrfA and ydhU did have a modest increase while two others didn't. [CITATION_1] . Glucosylglycerate is an osmoprotectant in bacteria and archaea and accumulates under salt stress and limited nitrogen availability [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However, most of our experiments were conducted in LB with amino acids constituting the main carbon source. We find it unlikely that synthesis of either the glycoside or disaccharide could occur without the appropriate substrate, and therefore is not likely involved in ΔmstA phenotypic suppression.",
